HEADWORD: Feebleness
<hw>Fee"ble*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or condition of
being feeble; debility; infirmity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That shakes for age and <qex>feebleness</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Feebly</ent>⟦br⟧
